backModal_main_2533175\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vtx1665702711411.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vtx1665702711411.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vtx1665702711411.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vtx1665702711411\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Identification Type\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The method used to identify the beginning of a subfield.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vtx1665702711411__section_w200ab1b5b1_w201ab1b5_w202ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Value</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Description</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">None</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Variable length techniques not used.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">String Identifier</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Use an ASCII string to identify variable length fields. You can specify the respective strings using the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Identifier</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">First Subfield Identifier</span>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">x</var>-byte binary length</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Binary length where <var class=\"keyword varname\">x</var> is a value from one through\n                           four.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">String Id. and <var class=\"keyword varname\">x</var>-byte binary length</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Use a combination of string identifiers and binary length.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">x</var>-byte binary length and String-Id</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vtx1665702711411__table_d692e1_d693e1_d694e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Use a combination of binary length and the string identifiers.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vtx1665702711411__section_c1m_yqh_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1019236e190\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vtx1665702711411__p_d7616e1_d7617e1_d7618e1\">You can choose to use string identification, length\n            identification, or a combination of the two. Choose the option that you want to use from\n            the list provided.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vtx1665702711411__p_d7619e1_d7620e1_d7621e1\">If the field does not include subfields, leave the\n            subfield entries empty. If the field is fixed length, leave all these entries empty.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vtx1665702711411__section_ogh_1rh_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1019236e202\">Applies to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"vtx1665702711411__ul_gty_1rh_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vtx1665702711411__li_d3698e1_d3699e1_d3700e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yzg1665702711012.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yzg1665702711012.html\" title=\"A Modeled Field Interface is a Development Object that defines a reusable value for the Database Interface property of a Database Field.\">Modeled Field Interface</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lnr1704360335272.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Variable-Length Fields</a><p>Variable-length fields store only the actual data in the field, and not the trailing spaces that would be added for a fixed-length field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsl1665702711481.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Field Identifier</a><p>ASCII string that marks a variable-length field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/chv1665702711551.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>First Subfield Identifier</a><p>ASCII string that marks the first subfield when using variable-length techniques.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533175\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533175\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Identification Type Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Identification Type The method used to identify the beginning of a subfield. Value Description None Variable length techniques not used. String Identifier Use an ASCII string to identify variable length fields. You can specify the respective strings using the Field Identifier and First Subfield Identifier . x -byte binary length Binary length where x is a value from one through four. String Id. and x -byte binary length Use a combination of string identifiers and binary length. x -byte binary length and String-Id Use a combination of binary length and the string identifiers. Description You can choose to use string identification, length identification, or a combination of the two. Choose the option that you want to use from the list provided. If the field does not include subfields, leave the subfield entries empty. If the field is fixed length, leave all these entries empty. Applies to Modeled Field Interface Related Links Variable-Length Fields Variable-length fields store only the actual data in the field, and not the trailing spaces that would be added for a fixed-length field. Field Identifier ASCII string that marks a variable-length field. First Subfield Identifier ASCII string that marks the first subfield when using variable-length techniques. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}